# Conformance Gates

## Pre-Implementation Gate (Spec Readiness)

Before writing any code for a feature, verify:

- [ ] Feature spec is written, reviewed, and approved.
- [ ] Data contracts (JSON Schema / types) are defined and valid.
- [ ] API contracts (OpenAPI / GraphQL) are defined and lint-free.
- [ ] Error contracts are defined for all failure modes.
- [ ] Behavior specs (Given-When-Then) cover happy path and error paths.
- [ ] Conformance tests are generated from specs.
- [ ] Architecture decisions are documented as ADRs referencing specs.
- [ ] Dependencies and blockers are identified.

## Spec Conformance Gate (Per Feature)

After implementing each feature, validate against specs:

### Contract Conformance
- [ ] API responses match the OpenAPI spec exactly (schema, status codes, headers).
- [ ] Request validation rejects payloads that don't match the request schema.
- [ ] Data shapes in the database match the data contracts.
- [ ] Error responses match the error envelope contract.
- [ ] UI components accept and emit exactly the contracted props/events.
- [ ] Integration calls match the consumer-driven contracts (Pact / contract tests).

### Behavior Conformance
- [ ] All Given-When-Then scenarios pass.
- [ ] Happy path acceptance criteria are met.
- [ ] Error path acceptance criteria are met.
- [ ] Edge cases defined in specs are handled.
- [ ] Error messages match the spec's error code catalog.

### Code Quality
- [ ] Types/interfaces are generated from or aligned with spec schemas.
- [ ] No linter errors or warnings.
- [ ] No hardcoded values that should come from spec definitions.
- [ ] No `TODO` or `FIXME` left without a tracking ticket.
- [ ] Dead code is removed. No commented-out blocks.

### Testing
- [ ] Conformance tests pass (spec-generated).
- [ ] Unit tests cover business logic and edge cases beyond specs.
- [ ] Integration tests verify component interactions match contracts.
- [ ] Tests are deterministic and isolated.
- [ ] Code coverage meets project threshold (aim for 80%+ on business logic).

### Security Conformance
- [ ] Authentication matches the spec's security schemes.
- [ ] Authorization matches the spec's endpoint-level security requirements.
- [ ] User input is validated against the request schemas.
- [ ] No secrets in code or configuration files.
- [ ] SQL injection, XSS, CSRF protections match security specs.

### Performance Conformance
- [ ] Response times meet the SLOs defined in specs (p50/p95/p99).
- [ ] Throughput meets the spec's capacity requirements.
- [ ] No N+1 queries. Database queries are optimized.
- [ ] API responses are paginated per the pagination contract.
- [ ] No memory leaks (cleanup in effects, unsubscribe, close connections).

### Accessibility Conformance (UI)
- [ ] Semantic HTML matches the UI contract's accessibility requirements.
- [ ] Interactive elements are keyboard-navigable per spec.
- [ ] Color contrast meets WCAG AA (4.5:1 minimum).
- [ ] Screen reader labels are present on all interactive elements.
- [ ] Focus management is correct for modals and dynamic content.

## Spec Consistency Gate (Cross-Feature)

Before integrating features, validate spec consistency:

- [ ] No conflicting data contracts between features (same entity, different shapes).
- [ ] Shared contracts (`$ref`) are used consistently across all API specs.
- [ ] Error codes are unique and don't collide across features.
- [ ] Authentication and authorization contracts are consistent.
- [ ] Pagination and filtering contracts follow the shared spec.

## Pre-Release Gate

Before deploying to production:

- [ ] All feature conformance gates pass.
- [ ] All spec consistency gates pass.
- [ ] E2E tests pass on critical user flows defined in behavior specs.
- [ ] Performance benchmarks meet SLOs from specs.
- [ ] Security audit checklist matches security specs.
- [ ] API documentation is auto-generated from specs and up to date.
- [ ] Specs are versioned and tagged with the release.
- [ ] Rollback plan is documented and tested.
- [ ] Monitoring and alerting are configured for SLO violations.

## Continuous Conformance

- Run spec linters (OpenAPI, JSON Schema) on every commit.
- Run conformance tests on every push (CI pipeline).
- Run contract tests on every PR.
- Run E2E behavior tests before every deployment.
- Validate spec-to-code drift weekly (automated spec conformance report).
- Review dependency vulnerabilities weekly.
